> These Honey Garlic Beef Meatballs are a crowd pleaser and is one to get the family round the
> dinner table for. Super simple to make, and easily customised to suit the kids too.

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or
use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine half the garlic, @honey{15%g}, @panko breadcrumbs{10%g},
@salt{1/4%tsp} and @water{1%tbsp}, then add the @British beef mince{240%g}. Season with
pepper and mix together with your hands.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Roll into evenly-sized balls, 5 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the meatballs onto a large #baking tray{}. When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf
until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove from the oven and set aside.

== Noodles and Veg ==

Meanwhile, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the
noodles.

Halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 3cm chunks.

Halve and peel the @onion{1}, then cut each half into 3 wedges.

When boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{2} to the water and cook until tender,
~{4%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them
sticking together.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the pepper chunks and onion, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry
until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Put the @hoisin sauce{96%g}, @rice vinegar{15%ml} and @soy sauce{15%ml} in a small bowl.
Add the @water{50%ml} and mix together.

Stir the remaining garlic into the veg pan and cook for ~{1%minute}, then add the
noodles, cooked meatballs and hoisin sauce.

Mix well to combine and cook until everything's piping hot and the sauce has thickened
to coat the noodles. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of
water if you feel it needs it.

== To Serve ==

Remove the pan from the heat. Taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Share the noodles and meatballs between your serving bowls and sprinkle over the
@roasted white sesame seeds{5%g}.

Enjoy!